gmx:name.gco:CharacterString: Feature catalog for State Highways (Segments), California, 2015

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: State Highways segments are coded with the district, county, route, alignment, and postmile
Concatenation of the Route and RteSuffix fields.
Unique identifier of underlying Linear Referencing layer. RouteID along with Measure fields can allow these points to be re-dynamically segment points.
A single-digit alpha code attached to the route as a suffix to identify special situations where there are parallel roads with the same route number operating simultaneously.
Postmile prefix. A single-digit alpha code attached to the postmile as a prefix to indicate changes in the highway alignment.
Duplicate postmile at meandering county line
Reposting of duplicate postmile at end of a route
Actual distance in miles (calculated from the running summation of postmiles) from the beginning of the route of the beginning of the highway segment.
Actual distance in miles (calculated from the running summation of postmiles)from the beginning of the route of the ending of the highway segment.
Falls on a right alignment (may be identical to left alignment)
Falls on a left alignment (may be identical to a right alignment).
Falls on a right independent alignment.
Falls on a left independent alignment.
